above a target

309
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,885
before unleashing their
missiles they greatly reduce

310
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:19,767
the chance of interception.

311
00:16:19,854 --> 00:16:22,314
This system leaves us
as exposed as I am now.

312
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:24,188
(men shudder)

313
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:25,687
‐ Wow, there’s nothing
like a highly detailed

314
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:27,648
technical explanation
from a lady in a swimsuit.

315
00:16:27,737 --> 00:16:29,487
‐ No details uncovered.

316
00:16:29,572 --> 00:16:31,282
Trust Miss Versanche
to reveal it all.

317
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:33,365
‐ [Man] Hey, shouldn’t you
be with the other pilots?

318
00:16:33,493 --> 00:16:35,083
‐ [Man] Um, well...

319
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:51,682
(whooshing)

320
00:16:51,761 --> 00:16:53,011
‐ Here they come.

321
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:54,717
‐ Rioko, why did you
take off like that?

322
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:56,057
‐ It’s my job!

323
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:02,862
