the only things I do well.

324
00:17:02,939 --> 00:17:03,689
Yahh!

325
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:09,324
Another one.

326
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:11,283
‐ When it comes to fighting,
you’re our first star.

327
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:13,374
If you’re good at
something then what’s wrong

328
00:17:13,491 --> 00:17:14,161
with doing it?

329
00:17:14,242 --> 00:17:15,202
‐ Everything.

330
00:17:15,284 --> 00:17:19,544
These are other humans
that I’m killing now.

331
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:22,172
In the end the only
thing that I’m good at

332
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:23,460
is killing other people.

333
00:17:23,543 --> 00:17:24,963
‐ Three remaining
units have arrived

334
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:26,254
into the combat air space.

335
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:27,959
Don’t give up now.

336
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:30,337
‐ [Rioko] What am I supposed
to do when this war is over,

337
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:33,394
if the only thing that I’m
good at is something horrible?

338
00:17:33,511 --> 00:17:34,681
If this is what I’m best at,

339
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:37,642
then I’d be better
off not living at all.

340
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:39,023
‐ You’re wrong.

341
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,140
We need you.

342
00:17:40,226 --> 00:17:41,306
You’re the glue that
holds the fabric

343
00:17:41,394 --> 00:17:42,394
of this team together.

344
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:43,980
We’d be lost without you.

345
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:44,653
‐ I would.

346
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:45,980
‐ Me too.

347
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:47,315
‐ Me three.

348
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,400
‐ You’re our best pilot.

349
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:50,026
You’re the star we follow.

350
00:17:50,111 --> 00:17:52,861
‐ [Man] More humanoid
fighters moving to intercept.

351
00:17:52,947 --> 00:17:54,107
That makes four total.

352
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,490
Should we alter
our mission, sir?

353
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:57,085
‐ No, we will continue
on as planned.

354
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:59,751
It is imperative that we
retrieve the test data.

355
00:17:59,829 --> 00:18:01,749
Don’t engage unless you have to.

356
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:03,582
But I want those
missiles dropped.

357
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:04,828
‐ [Men] Aye‐aye, sir!

358
00:18:06,294 --> 00:18:08,714
‐ I fight because I cannot
accept the alternative,

359
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:10,546
and it does not bother me

360
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:11,721
because I know that
my cause is just.

361
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:14,929
‐ Yeah, well, what
bothers me is the fact

362
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:18,602
that we’re stuck behind
this stupid desk.

363
00:18:18,681 --> 00:18:20,641
‐ There’s nothing
wrong in fighting

364
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,346
if you’re fighting for friends.

365
00:18:22,435 --> 00:18:23,565
‐ And family.

366
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:24,314
‐ You’ll find
something else someday.

367
00:18:24,437 --> 00:18:26,437
But until then...

368
00:18:29,150 --> 00:18:32,110
‐ [Rioko] Alright,
team, let’s get ’em.

369
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:41,117
‐ [Man] Operations,
request retrieval, sir.

370
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:42,833
